# Custom Block Registry Parity

**CRITICAL:** Any custom block added to `BLOCK_REGISTRY` must be registered in every canonical path. Drift causes blocks to render as hard-coded, unselectable, or missing settings.

## Required registrations (all must include the new block type)

1. `baserow-app/lib/interface/types.ts` — `BlockType` union
2. `baserow-app/lib/interface/registry.ts` — `BLOCK_REGISTRY` entry with `defaultConfig`
3. `baserow-app/lib/interface/block-config-types.ts` — typed config + `BlockConfigUnion` + `BLOCK_CONFIG_UNION_TYPES`
4. `baserow-app/lib/interface/assertBlockConfig.ts` — validation case
5. `baserow-app/lib/interface/blockPickerModel.ts` — picker category
6. `baserow-app/components/interface/BlockPickerPanel.tsx` — icon map (if custom icon)
7. `baserow-app/components/interface/BlockRenderer.tsx` — `case` + lazy import
8. `baserow-app/components/interface/settings/blockSettingsRegistry.tsx` — data + appearance renderers
9. `baserow-app/__tests__/interface-invariants.test.ts` — parity passes via `BLOCK_CONFIG_UNION_TYPES` vs registry
10. `baserow-app/__tests__/edit-mode-block-selection.test.ts` — marketing custom blocks list (when applicable)

## Edit-mode click guards (custom blocks with internal navigation)

Blocks with quick-action cards, links, or record opens **must** guard all interactive handlers in page layout edit mode:

```tsx
if (isEditing) return
// or: render <div> instead of <Link> when isEditing
```

Apply to: quick actions, view-all links, guidance CTAs, event/resource card buttons, record drawer opens.

## Tests to add/update per new block

- Registry/config union parity (`members_welcome` pattern in `members-welcome.test.ts`)
- `assertBlockConfig` accepts default config
- BlockRenderer `case` present
- Edit-mode: no navigation/drawer opens when `isEditing`
- View mode: actions still work

## Verification

```bash
npm test -- --run interface-invariants
npm test -- --run edit-mode
npm test -- --run members
```
